HEADWORD: Hydrosorbic
<hw>Hy`dro*sor"bic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hydro-</ets>, 2 + <ets>sorbic</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or designating, an acid obtained
from sorbic acid when this takes up hydrogen; <as>as,
<ex>hydrosorbic</ex> acid</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

